Package notes

Class TestingNote

java.lang.Object
notes.Note
notes.TestingNote
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Reversable, Versionable
public class TestingNote extends Note
Represents a testing note with test case, test status, and mandatory test option fields. This class extends the base Note class to provide specialized functionality for managing software testing documentation, test cases, and test execution tracking.
Since:
1.0

      public TestingNote() throws TitleLengthExceededException

      Throws:
      TitleLengthExceededException - if the default title exceeds the maximum allowed length

    • TestingNote

      public TestingNote(String title, String description, String text, String author, Calendar date, Calendar deadline, String testCase, TestingNote.TestStatus testStatus, boolean isMandatoryTest) throws TitleLengthExceededException
      Constructs a new TestingNote with the specified parameters.
      Parameters:
      title - the title of the testing note (must not exceed maximum length)
      description - a brief description of the test purpose
      text - detailed test description, steps, or expected results
      author - the author who created this test note (typically QA engineer or developer)
      date - the creation date of the test note
      deadline - the deadline for test execution (can be null if no deadline)
      testCase - the test case identifier, name, or detailed test case description
      testStatus - the initial status of the test (typically PENDING for new tests)
      isMandatoryTest - true if this test must pass before release, false for optional tests
      Throws:
      TitleLengthExceededException - if the title exceeds the maximum allowed length

    • updateStatus

      public void updateStatus(TestingNote.TestStatus status)
      Updates the execution status of this test case. This method should be called after test execution to record the result.

      Typical workflow:

      1. Create test with PENDING status
      2. Execute the test case
      3. Call updateStatus() with PASSED or FAILED based on results
      Parameters:
      status - the new test status to set. Should reflect the actual execution result of the test case.
      See Also:
      • TestingNote.TestStatus

    • toString

      public String toString()
      Returns a string representation of this TestingNote. The string includes all information from the parent Note class plus the testing-specific fields: test case, mandatory flag, and test status.

      The format includes:

      • All base Note information (title, description, author, dates, etc.)
      • Test Case: [test case information]
      • Is Mandatory: [true/false]
      • Test Status: [PENDING/PASSED/FAILED]
